        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SECTION 5.  OBLIGATIONS WITH MULTIPLE PERSONS
Art. 1786.  Several, joint, and solidary obligations
When an obligation binds more than one obligor to one obligee, or binds one obligor to more than one obligee, or binds more than one obligor to more than one obligee, the obligation may be several, joint, or solidary.</p>
        </content>
